---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
export const prerender = true;

const pageTitle = "Damilare Osibanjo — Personal Wiki";
const pageDescription = "Personal wiki for Damilare Osibanjo — systems programmer, security researcher, and compiler engineer.";
const pageUrl = "https://devdami.varityweb.com/wiki";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} canonical={pageUrl}>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-16 font-mono text-xs text-text leading-relaxed">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-12 text-center">
      <a href="/" class="text-text-muted hover:text-white transition-all duration-150 block mb-4">&lt;- home</a>
      <h1 class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest text-white uppercase mb-2">// wiki: damilare osibanjo</h1>
      <p class="text-text-muted lowercase">/dəˈmɪlərɛɪ ˌoʊʃɪˈbɑndʒoʊ/ · free personal encyclopedia</p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 items-start">
      <!-- Left 2 columns: Wiki Main Content -->
      <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-6">
        <!-- Biography & Early Life -->
        <section id="biography" class="bg-surface/30 border border-border/40 hover:border-accent/40 rounded-lg p-5 transition-all duration-500 ease-out space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-[10px] uppercase text-white tracking-widest">// 1. biography & early life</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted lowercase">
            Damilare Osibanjo (born 2008 in Nigeria) is a self-taught systems programmer, application security researcher, and compiler engineer. He is known for building systems tools, custom programming language compilers, cycle-accurate emulators, and disclosing critical security vulnerabilities in modern AI orchestrators.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted lowercase">
            Osibanjo began programming at age 12, initially developing online environments and custom scripting behaviors in Lua on the Roblox platform. This early phase provided him with exposure to event loops, shared state synchronization, and script execution mechanics. At age 14, he transitioned to Python scripting, where he spent roughly two years building automation tools, web scrapers, and backend APIs.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted lowercase">
            By age 15, Osibanjo grew dissatisfied with high-level runtime abstractions, garbage collectors, and unexplained memory overhead. He shifted his focus to low-level systems programming, teaching himself the fundamentals of operating systems, assembly language, memory management, and compilers. He subsequently transitioned to systems languages including Rust, Go, C, and Zig.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Notable Works -->
        <section id="notable-works" class="bg-surface/30 border border-border/40 hover:border-accent/40 rounded-lg p-5 transition-all duration-500 ease-out space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-[10px] uppercase text-white tracking-widest">// 2. notable works</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-white font-semibold lowercase">// carv language</h3>
              <p class="text-text-muted mt-1 leading-relaxed lowercase">
                Carv is an opinionated, statically-typed systems programming language designed to compile down to C99 specifically targeting ARM Cortex-M0–M7 microcontrollers as well as native host targets (x86_64). The compiler is written in ~6,250 lines of Go and features a custom Pratt parser, type inference, ownership tracking, borrow checking, state-machine based async/await, closures with environment capture, interfaces with vtable dispatch, and an arena allocator runtime.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-t border-border/20 pt-4">
              <h3 class="text-white font-semibold lowercase">// cve-2026-33017 (langflow rce)</h3>
              <p class="text-text-muted mt-1 leading-relaxed lowercase">
                Osibanjo discovered and disclosed CVE-2026-33017, a critical CVSS 9.8 remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability in Langflow (an open-source AI agent workflow platform). The vulnerability allowed unauthenticated attackers to execute arbitrary code server-side by abusing an unauthenticated endpoint (`POST /api/v1/build_public_tmp/&#123;flow_id&#125;/flow`) that processed node graphs. By injecting arbitrary Python code into Custom Component node definitions, the payload bypassed the frontend validator and executed code directly via the server's raw `exec()` sink without sandboxing.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-t border-border/20 pt-4">
              <h3 class="text-white font-semibold lowercase">// karion os kernel</h3>
              <p class="text-text-muted mt-1 leading-relaxed lowercase">
                Karion OS is a hobby bare-metal x86 operating system kernel written in Rust (transitioned from an initial C codebase). Built as a `no_std` Rust static library, it implements its own VGA text driver, GDT (Global Descriptor Table), IDT (Interrupt Descriptor Table), PIC (Programmable Interrupt Controller), memory paging, physical memory allocator, and a heap coalescing allocator. The kernel features a Unix-like shell, custom block filesystem, a text editor, a BASIC interpreter, and built-in text games.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-t border-border/20 pt-4">
              <h3 class="text-white font-semibold lowercase">// gbemu (game boy emulator)</h3>
              <p class="text-text-muted mt-1 leading-relaxed lowercase">
                A cycle-accurate Game Boy emulator written in Zig with zero external dependencies. The project implements cycle-accurate CPU instruction emulation, memory-mapped I/O, scanline PPU rendering, timer synchronization, and MBC1 memory bank controller support. The codebase explores hardware edge cases, audio wave channel quirks, and OAM DMA timing.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Technical Skills -->
        <section id="skills" class="bg-surface/30 border border-border/40 hover:border-accent/40 rounded-lg p-5 transition-all duration-500 ease-out space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-[10px] uppercase text-white tracking-widest">// 3. technical skills</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-white font-semibold min-w-[100px] lowercase block">systems:</span>
              <span class="lowercase">rust (safe/unsafe, no_std), zig (allocators, comptime), c (c99/c11, pointers), go (concurrency, internals)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-white font-semibold min-w-[100px] lowercase block">compilers:</span>
              <span class="lowercase">lexical analysis, pratt parsing, abstract syntax trees (ast), type checking, borrow checkers, arena allocation runtimes, c codegen</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-white font-semibold min-w-[100px] lowercase block">security:</span>
              <span class="lowercase">application pentesting, source code auditing, static analysis, command injection exploit chains, sandboxing mitigation (gvisor, firecracker)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-white font-semibold min-w-[100px] lowercase block">backend & dev:</span>
              <span class="lowercase">typescript, node.js, bun, python, linux infrastructure, docker, git, postgresql</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Philosophy -->
        <section id="philosophy" class="bg-surface/30 border border-border/40 hover:border-accent/40 rounded-lg p-5 transition-all duration-500 ease-out space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-[10px] uppercase text-white tracking-widest">// 4. philosophy</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed lowercase">
            Osibanjo advocates for understanding systems at the lowest feasible level of abstraction. He believes that working close to the hardware fundamentally changes how one designs at the application layer. His programming principles center around zero-dependency software, explicit code layouts, local-first computing, and avoiding implicit framework behaviors in favor of boring, predictable, and measurable code.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Right 1 column: Infobox + Table of Contents -->
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Infobox Sidebar -->
        <aside class="bg-surface/40 border border-border/60 rounded-lg p-5 space-y-4">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center text-center pb-4 border-b border-border/40">
            <img
              src="/icon.png"
              alt="damilare osibanjo"
              class="w-20 h-20 rounded-full object-cover border border-border/60 mb-3"
            />
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-xs lowercase">damilare osibanjo</span>
            <span class="text-[10px] text-text-muted mt-0.5 lowercase">systems developer</span>
          </div>
          
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[10px]">
            <div>
              <span class="text-white block lowercase">born:</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted lowercase">2008 (age 17) · nigeria</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span class="text-white block lowercase">occupation:</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted lowercase">systems programmer, security researcher, compiler engineer</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span class="text-white block lowercase">notable:</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted lowercase">carv language, cve-2026-33017, kiattp, game boy emulator</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>

        <!-- TOC Box -->
        <aside class="bg-surface/40 border border-border/60 rounded-lg p-4 space-y-3">
          <div class="text-white text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">// contents</div>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-[11px] text-text-muted">
            <li class="hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-150">
              1. <a href="#biography" class="hover:text-white underline">biography & early life</a>
            </li>
            <li class="hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-150">
              2. <a href="#notable-works" class="hover:text-white underline">notable works</a>
            </li>
            <li class="hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-150">
              3. <a href="#skills" class="hover:text-white underline">technical skills</a>
            </li>
            <li class="hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-150">
              4. <a href="#philosophy" class="hover:text-white underline">philosophy</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
